ALGORITHM (Text format)
Start the program.
Represent the graph using an adjacency list, where each node represents a room and each edge represents a path between rooms.
Choose the starting node from which the traversal begins.
Create an empty set called visited to keep track of visited nodes.
Create an empty queue to store the nodes that need to be explored.
Mark the starting node as visited and insert it into the queue.
Repeat the following steps until the queue becomes empty:
Remove the front node from the queue.
Display the removed node.
Visit each adjacent (neighboring) node of the current node.
If an adjacent node has not been visited:
Mark it as visited.
Insert it into the queue.
Stop when all reachable nodes have been visited and the queue becomes empty.
